				"paragraphStyle" : {
					"__type" : "textStyle"
				},
				"string" : "In 1971, Thomas Schelling published a paper entitled [\"Dynamic models of segregation\"](https://doi.org/10.1080/0022250X.1971.9989794) He explored one specific mechanism of racial segregation, by simulating what is often considered to be the first [agent-based model](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Agent-based_model). He performed his simulations manually, using coins he moved around on a piece of paper, and made no effort to define unambiguous rules for them."
			},
