				"string" : "The remaining pages provide a formalization of Schelling's model in Leibniz. It is not meant to be an implementation of the paper. It's rather what Schelling, or more likely Sakoda the computational pioneer, would write today *instead of* the 1972 paper (although all the sociological background is missing here)."
